On 1 April, the staff of the cmrf-fm radio station of Quebec, Canada, made a telephone link to Bill Gates on 1 April, claiming that he was Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien, and he had an intimate conversation with him for up to 10 minutes.
The topic covered the shortcomings of the world economy and the "Windows" operating system. At the same time, Bill Gates was invited to visit Quebec at an appropriate time.
The radio station broadcast the sound of the interview on the evening of 2 April and repeat it at the request of a wide audience the next day.
After the incident, he said that he never thought that it would be so easy to contact Bill Gates, and his assistant did not find out that it was just a "joke" of a foolish man.
