Computer crime caused the US to lose billions of US dollars last year.
WASHINGTON, April 7 (Xinhua) The "Computer Crime and Security Survey 2001" released by the United States on 7 April has caused US companies and government departments to suffer a loss of billions of dollars last year, a significant increase from the year 2000.
Computer systems in various parts of the United States have been exposed to computer virus attacks, denial of service attacks and the existence of various safety loopholes.
538 computer safety experts from enterprises, government departments and universities indicated that US companies and other organizations have to pay a high price each year for computer crimes.
Although the exact amount of the loss has not yet been finalized, 35 per cent of the sectors surveyed admitted that they had suffered losses totalling more than $3.78 billion, a substantial increase from nearly $26.56 billion in 2000.
The report, prepared jointly by the United States Computer Safety Association and the Federal Bureau of Investigation, did not provide an assessment of the losses suffered by individual users throughout the country.
Berber is defined as the official language of Algeria.
ALGIERS, April 8 (Xinhua) The Algerian parliament, at a joint meeting held here today, discussed and approved a draft constitutional amendment proposed by President Bouteflika.
In his speech at the meeting, Albanian Prime Minister Ben Fris pointed out that the adoption of the draft means that the cultural diversity of the country will be determined by legal means, which will help strengthen the unity of the Albanian people.
Berber is an indigenous resident of the North African region, and the number of Berber, currently residing in Algeria, accounts for about one sixth of the total population of the country.
The post-independence constitution provides that the Arabic language is the only official language, but is opposed by Berber.
In April of last year, a serious riot took place in the eastern part of the eastern part of the province of Berber.
Over a period of more than three months, more than 60 people have died and more than 2,000 people have been injured.
The local population requested that the constitution be established as an official language.
On 12 March this year, in a televised address to the nation, President Bouteflika promised to meet the requirements of Berber by amending the constitution.
